image.altText: Usman Khawaja raises his hands and helmet in celebration of an Ashes century.

items.synopsis: Usman Khawaja is elated with his first Test century in England, keeping Australia in the first Ashes Test at Edgbaston. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: Usman Khawaja scores first Ashes ton in England to lead Aussie fight back on day two

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A huge cry as Khawaja realised that ball had got through, his 14th four but the one that meant he reached his first century on English soil. "A masterful knock," says Jason Gillespie on ABC Sport. He really enjoyed that, and so he should, wheeling away and leaping in the air, waving his bat - it was an emphatic celebration. He even threw his bat away. Scenes. "It is hard to find a weakness in Usman Khawaja's game at the moment once he gets in. He is so, so composed," says Jim Maxwell on ABC Radio. A terrific century that has helped Australia out no end. 102 off 199 balls his total. So far.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Khawaja makes a century!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A magical ball from Moeen Ali! Drift away, turn back in and Green was bowled through the gate to the top of middle and leg stump. A terrific piece of bowling and Cameron Green has to go for 38 off 68.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: BOWLED HIM WITH A BEAUTY! GREEN HAS TO GO!

children.content: (Getty Images)
A magical ball from Moeen Ali!
Drift away, turn back in and Green was bowled through the gate to the top of middle and leg stump.
(Getty Images)
A terrific piece of bowling and Cameron Green has to go for 38 off 68.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Big session for Australia, thanks to Usman Khawaja and Travis Head. Cameron Green, too, was showing some intent late. Strangely, in the final over before the break. The English bowlers are struggling to elicit much action right now, and Khawaja and Green are both looking pretty solid out there. But so too was Travis Head. All it takes is one moment to change the game completely.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEA: Australia 4-188 (Khawaja 84, Green 21)

props.alt: Cameron Green completes a cricket shot.

children.content: (Getty)
Big session for Australia, thanks to Usman Khawaja and Travis Head.
Cameron Green, too, was showing some intent late. Strangely, in the final over before the break.
The English bowlers are struggling to elicit much action right now, and Khawaja and Green are both looking pretty solid out there.
But so too was Travis Head. All it takes is one moment to change the game completely.
